\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
iii)
\series default
 Suppose triangle 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is similar to triangle 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 and triangle 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 is similar to triangle 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $A,B$
\end_inset

 share the same angles, and 
\begin_inset Formula $B,C$
\end_inset

 share the same side angles, thus 
\begin_inset Formula $A,C$
\end_inset

 share the same side angles so 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 and 
